    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to use square tiles to find the area of rectangles. They use their knowledge of tiling to complete the tiling that is started in each rectangle. Students may use physical tiles on copies of the blackline master or reason directly on the images in the student book, which may not be the right size for physical tiles. The synthesis focuses on solidifying the idea that <strong>area</strong> is the number of square units that cover a flat figure with no gaps or overlaps.</p>
<p>This activity uses MLR1 Stronger and Clearer Each Time. Advances: reading, writing</p>
